  "accepted_findings": [
    "Deterministic collision-aware routing now compares every near branchlet and tertiary centerline against previously authored nearby segments before accepting it.",
    "The search preserves each original authored direction first, then tries bounded angular alternatives and small parent-axis attachment shifts instead of reducing the physical clearance thresholds.",
    "Across eight independent crown forms the final pass reroutes sixteen branchlets and nine hundred two tertiaries, leaving zero unresolved near-centerline conflicts.",
    "Every form satisfies the 1.2 cm near-branchlet and 0.6 cm near-tertiary clearance contracts; the family minima are 1.2181 cm and 0.6000 cm.",
    "The final UE 5.8 Metal run completes forty captures and validates forty-one generated assets with forty zero-error, zero-warning map checks."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "The physical near-centerline clearance gate passes, but closeups still contain visually tangled projected silhouettes and abrupt cylindrical junctions that read as procedural assembly rather than photoreal branch growth.",
    "The clearance audit does not yet cover parent-shoot, primary-branch, trunk-junction, leaf-card overlap, or screen-space occlusion quality, so it cannot by itself approve the closeup topology gate.",
    "The shared primary-branch cadence remains visible in whole-tree views and still needs per-form branch-origin and ramification grammar variation.",
    "The dense non-Nanite foreground family has no measured desktop or VR frame-time, memory, draw-call, overdraw, or culling evidence.",
    "Temporal branch-versus-leaf wind phase, amplitude bounds, motion vectors, and mixed native corridor ecology remain unvalidated."
  ],
